Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the transmission of data using spatial degrees of freedom and feedback channel state information, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a scheduling algorithm for multi-user MIMO systems, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a two-stage algorithm for user scheduling, which involves control of the system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions real-time applications, which are often related to multimedia. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the queueing performance of the proposed scheduling algorithm, which is related to performance analysis.
